Python and SQL Case Study: Building a Simple Data Analysis Pipeline

Setting Up the Database: Create a SQLite database and populate it with sample data.
Connecting to the Database: Use Python's sqlite3 module to connect to the database. 
Querying the Database: Execute SQL queries from Python to fetch data.
Analyzing the Data: Use pandas for data analysis.
Visualizing the Data: Use matplotlib to visualize the data.

Database Setup Script (setup_database.py)
Database Connection and Query Module (database.py)
Data Analysis Script (data_analysis.py)
Data Visualization Script (data_visualization.py)
Configuration File (config.py)

